SEC. 2. Section 15 of the same Act is hereby amended to read as follows:

âSEC. 15.

Tax Exemptions and Fee Privileges.

â Any existing law to the contrary notwithstanding, the transfer of NPAs from the F1 to an SPV, and from an SPV to a third party or dation on payment (dacion en pago) by the borrower or by a third party in favor of an F1 in favor of an SPV shall be exempt from the following taxes:

"(a) Documentary stamp tax on the abovementioned transfer of NPAs and dation in payment (dacion en pago) as may be imposed under Title VII of the National Internal Revenue Code of 1997;

"(b) Capital gains tax imposed on the transfer of lands and or other assets treated as capital assets as defined under Section 39 (A)(l) of the National Internal Revenue Code of 1997;

"(c) Creditable withholding income taxes imposed on the transfer of land and/or buildings treated an ordinary assets pursuant to Revenue Regulation No. 2-93, as amended;

"(d) Value added tax on the transfer of NPAs as may be imposed under Title IV of the National Internal Revenue Code of 1997 or gross receipts tax under Title V of the same Code, whichever is applicable.
